      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CARDIGAN DAN (1) is a talented colt who has impressively won his two Melton starts off a spell. Has led and cruised home by big margins in both of those so can take advantage of the inside draw. He'll be tough to catch. SOAP AND BUBBLES (9) could be close to a win after a series of top-four finishes at Melton, coming from this row for second last time. She is suited at a venue where she has won both attempts. BIZZNESS CLASS (11) was good in two outings over the Mildura carnival, winning well two back and placing last time. Tricky draw but can be competitive with even luck. FRUGAL FARE (10) has been racing consistently and goes very well here with three wins and a placing from four attempts so respect.",
